Scope
This privacy policy describes our privacy practices concerning the information that we collect through or related to Betabound.com, the Betabound web-based portal (my.betabound.com), Betabound social media pages, emails, and other communications with you related to Betabound (collectively, the
Betabound Sites
).
This policy does not describe our privacy practices related to Centercode.com, and our Centercode social media pages (collectively, the
Centercode Sites
), and information we gather related to Centercode employment, vendor relationships, and business services. If you’re a visitor to the Centercode Sites or a vendor, business contact, or job applicant, please visit the
Centercode Privacy Policy
to learn about the privacy practices that apply to you.
Finally, we offer our platform to subscribing customers that use their own instance of the Centercode Platform to develop and manage their own test communities and test programs. Their use of our platform and the use by their authorized users is outside the scope of this privacy policy. If you encounter our platform outside of Betabound, you should review the privacy policy of the company using our platform before creating an account. To learn more about the data that we hold and process for our customers on their behalf, please review our
Customer Data Handling Privacy Policy
.
The Data We Collect and Receive
To operate and enable your use of the Betabound Sites, provide testing services to our customers, operate our business, contact you about Betabound, and for other legitimate business interests described in this policy, we receive and collect certain information from you and about you, including Betabound Profile information, Test Feedback, and other information, which includes
Personal Data
.
Except as described below for California consumers, when we use the term
Personal Data
, we mean information relating to an identified or identifiable individual (e.g., name, email address, phone number, location data, mailing address)
(or as otherwise defined in the laws that apply)
.
By submitting or providing Personal Data or other information to us, you are representing that you have authority to do so and that we have full authorization to use this information in accordance with this privacy policy, even if the information relates to other individuals or entities. You agree to provide and maintain complete and accurate information, and understand that you are solely responsible for the data that you provide to us.
Betabound Community Member Information
In order to create a Betabound Community Member account, we require you to provide both basic account information (such as your first and last name, email address, username and password, time zone, country, and date of birth), as well as Betabound Basic Profile information (such as preferred operating system and mobile platform, information about products you are interested in testing, and, optionally, gender). You have the option of completing an Extended Profile, where you provide additional information (including Personal Data, such as complete residential address, phone number, languages spoken, social media handles, home ownership and family information, details about your education, employment information, information about experience with technology and with testing, and similar information).
At different times, we may also ask you to complete voluntary surveys seeking more information, including Personal Data, about your interest in and qualifications for tests that may be conducted by us on behalf of our customers. While you do not need to provide Extended Profile and additional information, providing additional information can increase the number of test opportunities available to you because we can match your information with the test participant requirements for specific tests.
In addition, sometimes additional information is required for you to be eligible to participate in certain tests. For example, you are required to complete an Extended Profile, including phone number and address, if you wish to participate in any test that involves sending a physical product to you.
We own and control the information that you provide as a part of your Betabound registration, profile, and completion of other Betabound community-level member questionnaires or surveys and share this information as described below in How We Use and Share Personal Data. We call this information your Betabound Profile.
However, your Test Feedback (any information that we collect or you provide during or in connection with applying for, and/or participating in a specific test) is collected by us on behalf of the company that has hired us to manage its test, and we process this information on behalf of that customer in accordance with our separate agreement with our customer.
Where we process your information on behalf of our customer, or where you share your personal data or agree that we may share your personal data with our customer, the data collection and privacy practices of our customer (such as those disclosed in its privacy policy and any other agreement(s) you are asked to enter into with our customer) control as between you and our customer. For more information about the information that we hold and process for our customers on their behalf, please read about our
Customer Data Handling Privacy Policy
.
If you have any questions about the privacy practices of any Centercode customer, please contact our customer about your inquiry.
Becoming a Betabound Community Member is entirely voluntary. If you do not wish to provide the required information, you should not become a Betabound Community Member. If you do not wish to provide any optional additional requested information, you should not do so.
Referrals and Ambassador Program Information
Through our Betabound Ambassador program and our participant Referral program, we ask our members to voluntarily provide email addresses of friends and others who they’d like to refer to us as potential testers and Betabound members. Do not provide us with email addresses unless you have the authority to do so.
Test Announcement Information
If you provide information to us so that we can announce your third-party user test, we may collect, process, and use the Personal Data and other information that you provide to us, such as your contact information, company information, and product information. You represent that you have authority to provide us with the information that you supply and authorize us to post the information you provide to us on the Betabound Sites. You are solely responsible for the contents of the data that you provide to us.
Other Information Collected
As you interact with us regarding your Betabound account or your interest in our offerings, such as through Betabound.com, Betabound social media pages, emails, and other communications outside of your Betabound account, we may gather Personal Data from you, such as your name, phone number, and email address, and any other information you voluntarily provide to us. Also, we passively collect data as disclosed below in Cookies, IP Addresses, and Other Passive Information collection.
How We Use and Share Personal Data
This section describes how we use and share information within the scope of this policy.
Betabound Community Member Information
When you provide your email to us during the Betabound registration process, you are agreeing to allow us to use the information that you provide, including Personal Data, to determine if you may match the profile for participation in tests conducted by or on behalf of our customers. When we believe you might be interested in our customers’ tests, we will contact you about these opportunities using the contact information you have provided to us in your Betabound Profile.
We may also send you newsletters, announcements, or communications, including by email and text message, that we believe may be of interest to you. If at any time you no longer wish to receive announcements about these test opportunities or other communications, or wish to modify your account preferences, you can follow the instructions under
Updating Email Preferences
and/or
Removing Your Betabound Account
below to either modify your preferences or terminate your Betabound Community Member account.
Unless and until you express interest in participating in, accept an invitation to participate in, or actually participate in a test being conducted by Centercode on behalf of a Centercode customer and in doing so indicate your willingness to share your Personal Data, we will not share your Personal Data in any way that identifies you to any Centercode customer.
However, once you indicate your willingness to share your personal data in connection with a test being conducted by Centercode on behalf of its customer, you are agreeing to allow us to share the information you have provided to us through your Betabound registration, including your profile information and any other Betabound qualification survey, community survey, questionnaire, form, email or other communication about your profile, with the Centercode customer for which we are conducting a test.
We provide this data to enable our customers to identify ideal test candidates and, if you are selected as a test participant, for our customers to include this data as a part of their test data.
Once shared with our customer, the customer determines its own policies and practices for the use, sharing, and disclosure of this information, and Centercode does not control how it chooses to use, share, or disclose this information. Before you apply to participate in any test, you should read the company’s privacy policy or other privacy disclosure carefully so that you understand how your information, including your Personal Data, will be used and shared by this third party
.
In addition to this profile information being shared with our customers as described above, sometimes during a test, a subset may be shared with other test participants where the test includes collaborative activities, such as group chats and discussions. During these activities, selected profile information, which can include your full name, username, and any text or file-based feedback you provide in that group activity, may be visible to other participating testers. If you are not comfortable with this, do not participate in the group activity or share text or files in the group activity.
Referrals and Ambassador Program Information
We use email addresses we received through our Referral or Ambassador Program to contact these potential new test participants to see if they are interested in joining Betabound. If you receive an email from us and wish to be removed from our interest list, please contact us at optout@betabound.com and identify that you received a referral email and wish for us to delete your email address.
Test Announcement Information
When you provide information to us to announce your third-party user test, we use this information to publicly announce the test on Betabound.com.
Please do not provide any Personal Data, confidential data, or other information that you do not want to reveal to the public at large.
Betabound Visitor, Business, and Other Contact Information
We use contact information that you have provided as a visitor to the Betabound Sites or through your business or other contacts to contact you to discuss your interest in Betabound and Centercode services, and to send you information such as announcements of opportunities and events regarding Betabound and product and service tests. Where you provide us with your contact information, we may also send you community newsletters and updates. If at any time you no longer wish to receive these communications, you can follow the instructions under
Updating Email Preferences
.
Other Use and Sharing
We may also use or share information you provide to us for other legitimate interests including:
to create an account you have requested;
to send administrative information to you, such as changes to our terms, conditions, and policies;
to respond to your inquiries and fulfill your requests, such as to send you requested materials and newsletters, as well as information about our services and businesses;
to service your account, including maintaining records of any agreements you enter into;
to communicate with you and provide you with all necessary or helpful information, including on our customer’s behalf as their service provider;
to send, install, remove, or retrieve any test product, device, or software on our customer’s behalf as their service provider;
to personalize your experience on the Betabound Sites, such as by presenting opportunities or content tailored to you;
as disclosed below in Cookies, IP Addresses, and Other Passive Information Collected;
regarding the general level of participation of Betabound Community Members in tests that we conduct, for our customers to assist in determining whether they are a good candidate for other tests we might perform for customers;
for other internal business purposes, such as data analysis, audits, detecting security incidents, protecting against malicious, deceptive, fraudulent, or illegal activity, network, information, and system security, debugging, developing new products, enhancing, improving or modifying the Centercode Platform and our Betabound Sites and services, identifying usage trends, determining the effectiveness of our campaigns, and operating or expanding our business activities;
in connection with company transactions such as asset sales, reorganizations, mergers, joint ventures, assignments, financings, dispositions of stock, and other changes of control, where Personal Data and other information is transferred to third parties for legitimate purposes in connection with the transactions;
as we believe to be necessary or appropriate under applicable law, including laws outside of your country of residence, to comply with legal process, to respond to the requests of courts or governmental authorities, to enforce our terms and conditions, to protect our operations, rights, privacy, safety, customers, or property (or that of others), and to allow us to pursue available remedies or limit damages we may sustain; and
for other purposes you have specifically agreed to.
Aggregated or De-Identified Information
Where data is aggregated or de-identified so that it is no longer reasonably associated with an identified or identifiable natural person, we may use and disclose it for any business purpose, except as otherwise prohibited under applicable law. Typically, this would be used for research purposes, or to promote our community, but we may have other business uses.
How We Share Data with Our Third-Party Service Providers and Partners
We contract with third-party service providers and partners who provide services to us in accordance with our instructions, including our cloud hosting provider for the Betabound web portal (Amazon Web Services), our customer relationship management (CRM) provider for companies interested in advertising their tests on Betabound.com (HubSpot), our shipping providers (e.g., UPS, FedEx, USPS), test application distribution (e.g., TestFairy), test product installers (where you agree to allow the installation of a test product as a part of a test), general office services such as email and file storage (Google), distribution of any thank you incentives to successful test participants (e.g., Amazon and Tango Card), and as discussed below in connection with cookies.
These third parties may have access to your data (including Personal Data) for the purpose of providing services to us or to our customer whose product or service you are testing, and in compliance with our documented instructions. We diligently choose these third-party service providers, evaluate their privacy, security, and confidentiality practices, and enter into agreements with them specifying their obligations. In addition, your information is shared as described below in connection with cookies.
Cookies, IP Addresses, and Other Passive Information Collected
Like many companies, we use cookies (small data files stored on your computer), logging, and similar tools to collect and analyze information about our visitors and community members. This information is used to operate the Betabound Sites, to prevent fraud and misuse of our services, to measure how people use the Betabound Sites, to analyze how people respond to our emails and other communications, to analyze trends, to improve the Betabound Sites and our services, and to improve your overall experience.
Third-Party Cookies and Opting Out
Google Analytics Cookies: We use Google Analytics cookies, which are cookies that allow us to analyze how our visitors and users interact with the Betabound Sites, including Betabound.com and the Betabound portal (my.betabound.com). Your activity as you navigate is tracked by Google Analytics. The information generated about your usage is transmitted to Google and is used to compile statistical reports on activity on the Betabound Sites to help us improve these sites, the information we offer, and your experience. The information we receive from Google Analytics is aggregated data and we cannot use it to individually identify any particular visitor or user. We encourage you to read the
Google Privacy Policy
.
HubSpot Cookies: We also use HubSpot cookies in connection with certain forms on Betabound.com that are directed at visitors from businesses interested in advertising their tests on Betabound.com. These HubSpot-placed cookies enable your interactions with those forms and the data you enter into those forms and information generated about your usage is transmitted to HubSpot in the United States. We encourage you to read the
HubSpot Privacy Policy.
AddThis Cookies: When you visit Betabound.com, we use AddThis cookies to enable sharing links to articles, test opportunities, and other content on Betabound.com with others via social media sites. When you visit Betabound.com, AddThis obtains information through these cookies about your browsing, both on our site and after you leave our site, and about your device, including your browser and device type, IP address, and geolocation. Information about your usage of our site is provided to us by AddThis on an aggregated basis that does not identify individual visitors or users, providing us with statistical reports on activity on the Betabound Sites to help us improve these sites, the information we offer, and our visitors’ experience. AddThis uses the information it obtains in accordance with its privacy policy. In addition, any social media site you interact with when sharing content will use its own cookies in connection with their services as well. We encourage you to read the
AddThis Privacy Policy
and the privacy policies of any social media site that you interact with through Betabound.com.
The services above may work by use of standard tracking technologies other than cookies, such as web beacons, clear gifs, pixels, and similar tracking technologies in addition to or instead of cookies.
Opting Out of Cookies: You can optionally opt out from your data being collected and reported by
Google Analytics
,
AddThis
, or
HubSpot
. Or, to learn generally how to opt out of cookies and other tracking technologies using your browser settings, you may wish to visit the FTC’s Online Tracking informational page or, if you reside in the European Union, to visit http://www.youronlinechoices.eu/.
Centercode Mandatory Session Cookies and Usage Data
When accessing your account on Betabound, the platform uses session cookies to grant you access to and secure your account. These cookies allow us to uniquely identify you following the entry of your username and password so that you may access your account. Session cookies are required to use our services.
In addition, when you log in to these accounts, our servers automatically log typical HTTP information, including your Internet Protocol (IP) address, a unique device identifier (a UUID), your device name, operating system type and version, network type, country of origin, information about how you use your account (e.g., the pages you view, the links you click, the dates and times of your requests and referral URL, and other actions you take), the error messages you receive or problems you encounter, and similar data.
We use this information to provide our services and support to our customers and users. We also use this information to monitor the regions from which you navigate your account, to identify you when you are using your account, to enhance our security and service performance, and for audit, compliance, investigations, and customer support purposes. Where requested by our customer, we may share relevant log data with our customers for audit, compliance, investigations, and customer support purposes.
We also use de-identified or aggregated log data gathered about the general use of our services for internal business purposes such as developing and enhancing our products and services, identifying usage trends, and for other legitimate business purposes.
Do Not Track
We do not currently respond to “Do Not Track” browser signals.
Security
We take the security of the Personal Data that we hold very seriously. We maintain a written security policy for the security, integrity, and protection of the Personal Data we hold against unauthorized disclosure or loss. We have put in place physical, technical, and organizational processes and measures designed to safeguard all Personal Data.
When accessing an account on Betabound via a supported web browser, Transport Layer Security (TLS) is used to protect information using both server authentication and data encryption to help ensure data is safe and secure in transit.
We host Betabound, on cloud-based servers located in a secure data center environment using a firewall and other advanced technology designed to prevent interference or access from outside intruders. We also require verified email addresses, unique usernames, and strong passwords for account authentication.
These safeguards help prevent accidental or unlawful destruction, loss, alteration, unauthorized disclosure of, or access to the Personal Data that we hold. However, you should be aware that no security procedures or protocols are guaranteed to be 100% secure, and there is always some risk assumed when you share information. You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality and security of your username and password.
If you have reason to believe that your interaction with us is no longer secure, your account has been compromised, or you would like more information about our security practices, please
contact us immediately
. If any Personal Data under our control is compromised as a result of a breach of security, we will investigate the situation and, where appropriate or required by law, notify those individuals whose information may have been compromised and take other steps in accordance with applicable laws and regulations.
Updating Email Preferences
Betabound Community Members can modify their email preferences to unsubscribe from emails announcing tests conducted directly by Centercode customers themselves. Once you have completed your account registration, you can do this under the
User Profile
link on the left side of your account home page, in the Basic Profile. If you are not a Betabound Community Member or otherwise require assistance or want to opt out of receiving other emails or communications from us, please contact us at
optout@betabound.com
and we will respond promptly.
Removing Your Betabound Account
If you would like to remove your Betabound account entirely and stop receiving test announcements entirely, you can do so by using the
Remove Your User Account
feature on the right side of your
Account Settings page
, or by navigating to
https://betabound.com/optout
. If you have another request regarding your Personal Data, please notify us at
privacy@betabound.com
so that we may consider and respond to your request in accordance with applicable law.
Data Retention
We will retain your Personal Data for a period consistent with the original purpose of collection, including to pursue our legitimate business interests, comply with our legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce applicable agreements. For example, we will retain Betabound Profile information and other information collected in connection with your Betabound account as long as you maintain a Betabound account, and thereafter for the period of time that we need to pursue legitimate business interests, conduct audits, comply with and demonstrate compliance with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce agreements. We retain information derived from cookies and other tracking technologies for a reasonable period of time from the date such information was created.
We retain data that we hold on our customer’s behalf (e.g., the Test Feedback you provide to our customer) in accordance with our customer’s instructions and as required by applicable law.
Deleted data stored in our backup systems will be automatically deleted within a reasonable period of time during our backup procedures, except as otherwise required by applicable law.
Data Modification and Deletion; Other Rights of European Residents
Betabound Community Members may log in to their accounts to delete or amend certain types of Personal Data and information in their Betabound Profile at any time using the functionalities provided.
Individuals located in certain countries and localities, including those residing in the European Union, the European Economic Area, the United Kingdom, and Switzerland (“
European Residents
”), have certain statutory rights regarding their Personal Data. For European Residents, reference to
Personal Data
in this privacy policy is equivalent to Personal Data as defined in the EU General Data Protection Regulation
(including as it forms part of the United Kingdom domestic law)
or any successor or enacting legislation (the “
GDPR
”).
Subject to any exemptions provided by law, these individuals may have the right to request access to their Personal Data, or seek to update, delete, or correct Personal Data. If your request relates to Personal Data that we control within the scope of the GDPR, such as Betabound Profile information of a European Resident, your rights may be exercised by contacting us at
privacy@betabound.com
.
Any European Resident who is dissatisfied with our handling of a request regarding Personal Data within the scope of the GDPR, has a right to lodge a complaint with his or her local data protection authority responsible for monitoring the application of the GDPR.
If your request relates to information that we hold on our customer’s behalf, you must contact our customer, the data controller, for assistance with your request. You may contact us at
privacy@betabound.com
for assistance contacting our customer.
For your protection, we may need to take additional steps to verify your identity before implementing any request relating to your Personal Data. If you have designated an authorized agent to exercise your rights on your behalf, please note that to protect your Personal Data, we
will need to verify that your authorized agent has permission from you to make requests on your behalf, and we may need to also verify your authorized agent’s identity. If we are unable to do so, and you have not received a response from us, please contact us directly regarding your request. We will respond to your request promptly, and in no more than 30 days from your request, subject to applicable law. Please note that we may need to retain certain information for recordkeeping purposes, such as retaining copies of agreements you have entered into with us and/or for audit and investigation purposes, or in the event of a court order or requirement of law.
Deleted or updated Personal Data stored in our backup systems will be automatically deleted or updated within a reasonable period of time during our backup procedures, except as otherwise required by applicable law.
California
and Similar State
Privacy Rights
This section
describes the rights of individuals who are California residents under the California Consumer Privacy Act, as amended by the California Privacy Rights Act (the “CCPA”), and residents of other states or regions of the United States with similar applicable privacy laws with respect to their Personal Data.
It describes how we collect, use, and share
these individuals’
Personal Data in connection with the Betabound Sites in our role as a business, and the rights applicable to such residents. If you are unable to access this Privacy Policy due to a disability or any physical or mental impairment, please contact us and we will arrange to supply you with the information you need in an alternative format that you can access.
Categories of Personal Data
We have collected the following statutory categories of Personal Data in the past twelve (12) months:
Identifiers, such as first and last name, mailing address, email address, user identification, and phone number. We collect this information directly from you, or in the case of email addresses we received as a part of our referral program, from another Betabound user who has provided us with your email.
Protected legal characteristics, such as age/date of birth and sex and/or gender. We collect this information directly from you.
Commercial information, such as information about products and services you purchased, obtained, or considered purchasing that might be relevant to testing. We collect this information directly from you.
Internet activity or network information, such as browsing and search history within the Betabound Sites, and information about your interaction with our Betabound Sites. We collect this information directly from your device.
Geolocation data, such as your physical address that you provide to us, and by receiving IP address information from your device.
Audio and visual data in the form of photos, videos, and audio-recordings, that you provide to us during a test. We collect this information directly from you.
Employment information, such as your employer and employment history. We collect this information directly from you.
Education information, such as your educational level. We collect this information directly from you.
Other information, such as information about home ownership and household composition, information about your primary language(s), your social media handles, information about your experience with technology and testing, and similar information. We collect this information directly from you.
Inferences.
Other Personal Data you voluntarily provide to us in instances when you interact
with us through the Betabound Sites or other online methods, by phone, chat, email, or
mail in the context of receiving help through our support channels or offering feedback to us through the Betabound Sites.
How We Use and Share Your Personal Data
The business and commercial purposes for which we collect this information are described above in How We Use and Share Your Personal Data . The categories of third parties that have access to this information as our service providers for a business purpose are described above in How We Use and Share Your Personal Data
Your California
and Similar State Law
Rights
Based on where you reside, you may have certain rights regarding the Personal Data we collect or maintain about you, such as those listed below. Please note these rights are not absolute, and there may be cases when we decline your request as permitted by law.
Right of Access and Data Portability Rights: This is the right to request that we disclose what categories of Personal Data we have collected, used and disclosed about you, including:
the categories of sources for this Personal Data,
our legitimate business or commercial purpose for collecting or sharing this Personal Data,
the categories of third parties with which we share this Personal Data,
the specific pieces of your Personal Data we collected about you (a data portability request), and
if we sold or disclosed your Personal Data for a legitimate business purpose,
a list disclosing the sale(s) that identifies the Personal Data that each category of recipient purchased, and
disclosures made for a legitimate business purpose, identifying the Personal Data categories that each category of recipient obtained.
Right of Deletion: This is the right to request that we delete Personal Data collected or maintained by us, subject to certain exceptions.
Right to Non-Discrimination: You will not receive any discriminatory treatment when you exercise one of your privacy rights under the CCPA
and similar state laws.
Centercode does not sell your Personal Data to third parties.
We engage certain trusted third parties to perform functions and provide services to us. We may share your Personal Data with these third-party service providers, but only to the extent necessary to perform these functions and provide these services. We require these third parties to maintain the privacy and security of the Personal Data they process on our behalf. These disclosures for business purposes include disclosures of all Personal Data categories described above for auditing/compliance, hosting of the Betabound Sites and maintenance/security services, error monitoring, debugging, and performance monitoring, and your full name, username, and email for communication with you about your account and other support and for distribution of any thank you gifts for successful test participation. We also share your Personal Data that you have provided to us in connection with your Betabound account and profile with our customers who have hired Centercode to manage their product or service tests, but only after you have expressed your willingness to share your Personal Data, and these customers have agreed to only use this Personal Data in connection with their product or service test.
How to Exercise Your California and Similar State Law Privacy Rights
If you would like to access this policy in an alternative format or wish to exercise your privacy rights
under California or similar US state laws
, please contact us at privacy@betabound.com or (800) 705-6540 or reach us by using the methods provided in Questions or Concerns below.
Please be aware that when you make a request, we’ll take steps to verify that you are authorized to make the request.
You must provide sufficient detail that allows us to properly understand, evaluate, and respond to your request. We cannot respond to your request or provide you with Personal Data if we cannot verify your identity or authority to make the request and confirm the Personal Data relates to you. Making a request does not require you to create an account with us. We will only use Personal Data provided in the request to verify your identity and authority to make the request.
Links to Third-Party Sites
The Betabound Sites and emails that come from us contain links to other websites on the Internet. For example, on Betabound, we collect and organize a wide variety of test opportunities from all over the world, so we often announce opportunities for third parties, including those that are our customers and those that are not our customers.
We announce these opportunities through Betabound and also in other communications to you, such as in emails. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of all such third parties and any agreement(s) that you are asked to enter into in connection with any test or participant community membership.
Please note that we are not responsible for the privacy policies and collection, use, and disclosure practices (including the data security practices) of these third parties, including third parties that are our customers.
Data of Children
The Betabound Sites are not intended for use by minors under the age of 16. We do not knowingly or specifically collect information from these minors through the Betabound Sites or otherwise. If you believe that we have mistakenly or unintentionally collected information from minors or have any questions or concerns regarding the use of our services to collect information from minors, please contact us at
privacy@betabound.com
so that we may investigate and delete the information from our servers as necessary.
International Transfer of Data
The Personal Data and other information we collect from you is used, stored, and/or processed by us in the United States, where we are located. In addition, in the circumstances described in this privacy policy where your Personal Data and other information is transferred to a third party (including our customer), this data may also be used, stored, and/or processed outside of the United States in any country in which the third party has facilities or engages service providers. These countries may not offer the same legal protections offered in your country and may be considered by your country to offer insufficient legal protections.
European Residents have a right to withdraw their consent to cross-border transfers of their data, and if you wish to do so with respect to your Personal Data that we control, you may contact us at
privacy@betabound.com
. The withdrawal of consent will not affect the lawfulness of actions based on your consent prior to your withdrawal.
If your request relates to information that we hold on our customer’s behalf (e.g., Test Feedback), you must contact our customer, the data controller, for assistance.
Changes to Our Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to change this privacy policy. If we make changes to this policy, you will find the revised privacy policy posted on the Betabound Sites, along with the effective date of the revised privacy policy. Your use of and access to the Betabound Sites and the Centercode Platform after any changes become effective will be considered your acceptance of those changes and will constitute your agreement to be bound by the new or modified privacy policy.
Questions or Concerns
Questions about this Privacy Policy or our information practices should be directed to Centercode by emailing
privacy@betabound.com
or by mailing us at
23422 Mill Creek Drive, Suite 105, Laguna Hills, CA 92653 ATTN: Privacy Policy
.
Alternatively, to communicate with our Data Protection Officer, please email
dpo@betabound.com
, or by mail at
23422 Mill Creek Drive, Suite 105, Laguna Hills, CA 92653 ATTN: DPO
, or by phone at
(800) 705-6540
.
